@julianhyde 
I don't see the details of the check error, I can only see the code that can't pull the PR, so I can't help now.

By the way, in [Apache pulsar](https://github.com/apache/pulsar/pull/4281), we can re-checks the PR by commenting on keywords like `rerun java8 tests`. I hope that calcite can also handle this, thank you!

@asereda-gs any idea when can we close this PR? I notice that Calcite 1.20.0 release is coming.

Btw, I doubt there's enough time to merge [CALCITE-3080](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CALCITE-3080), may be better idea to make below change now, any thoughts?

```
interface KafkaRowConverter {
RelDataType rowDataType();
Object[] toRow(ConsumerRecord<K, V> message);
}
```

@XuMingmin it is fine if we redefine `KafkaRowConverter` interface after 1.20 (Ie address [CALCITE-3080](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CALCITE-3080)). 

It is the reason why I prefer to mention in 1.20 release notes that Kafka Adapter is currently in "preview mode" (some API might change). 

Pls rebase this PR (there are some conflicts)

@wenhuitang I will check.

Please add you name to commit message. It should say:
> [CALCITE-2460] [CALCITE-2459] Add TO_BASE64 / FROM_BASE64 SQL functions (FirstName LastName)
